crafts</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">April 20, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Solid plugin that helped me optimize my website for Google, increasing hits and lead generation. Now, I\'m using it across all of my different sites!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">They use number of keywords as a selling point but they aren&#039;t added to pages</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/malakmsah\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/50ee6b89d4f9f389ba5956cc24cea704?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/50ee6b89d4f9f389ba5956cc24cea704?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/malakmsah\" class=\"reviewer-name\">malakmsah</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">April 19, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">They trick people to buy this plugin by saying that you are allowed to add more than one keyword, but they don\'t add it to the web pages. They say that google stopped following meta keywords, so why lying and trick people to buy the plugin?!!!!!! This is scam</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info